title: Border.Security.AU.Front.Line.S14E05.PDTV.x264.Hector.mp4
description:
Folks, please note that the numbering given by TV Rage is completely different. I have no idea why they number it the way they do. So, as confusing as this is, please go by the accurate synopsis that I got at the time I capped these shows from here http://www.yourtv.com.au/guide/restofday/

A lively man from the US arrives on a tourist visa, 
but Immigration believes he may be here to work illegally. 
And despite his claim of a clean criminal record, officers findings prove otherwise. A shipment from Hong Kong ostensibly containing three standard household doors 
provokes officers' interests when one of the doors is heavier than the others. An X-ray shows there may be organic matter concealed inside. Then, two men from the Philippines arrive for a holiday after spending time working in Papua New Guinea, but Customs and Border Protection officers are concerned about 
their last-minute flight changes and lack of knowledge about what to see and do in Brisbane.
